<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-01-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="765" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d765">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Department
                                        of State</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-01-04"><hi rend="italic">January 4,
                                1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In an interview with the minister of Turkey to-day he assured me
                            positively that the Turkish Government has not made and will not make
                            arrests except so far as necessary to effect deportation. If
                            imprisonments occur otherwise you will insist on fulfillment of this
                            promise.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>